-->Fucntions:
A function is something which includes specific task.
--> Why are functions so important?
1--Divide and conquer.
2--reuse 
3--Abstraction
4--To improve the readability of the code 
----> Defining a functions 
A function has two parts : Header And Body
-- like int compare(int a, b)
Where header has the return type, name,input values.
And :: {

    BODY::: where it performs the tasks
}

-->Return Value:
Every function has a return type and value.
Every function can return only one value.
Every function can have multiple return staements.
--Void(ehich is emptyness)
i.e return type is "Void"
